The bishop added that it was "essential" the cathedral, which costs Â£1.5m a year to run, "lives within its means".
He said the cathedral's "situation in Exeter is acute because, unlike some other cathedrals, it has no large endowments".
The bishop has ordered a "change of culture" at the cathedral and wants a progress report from the chair of the Cathedral Council, which governs the cathedral, next April.
